name: Suspicious Tomates Narbonnaises
desc: A dish of meat and vegetables. Each dully colored tomato seems to be almost trembling, as though it wants to open its mouth and sob at what it has become. Even worse, the ground meat inside tastes like wood chips. There's four of these cup-like tomato abominations, just how should they be dealt with?

customize.name: Recipe: Tomates Narbonnaises
customize.desc: A detailed step-by-step recipe for making Tomates Narbonnaises.

customize.name: Onion
customize.desc: A spherical vegetable. As vengeance for cutting it, it will make you cry, no matter how brave you are.

customize.name: Tomato
customize.desc: A bright red ingredient that gives a tangy kick. Yes, the "fruit or vegetable" debate is still going...

customize.name: Raw Meat
customize.desc: A fresh chunk of meat. Handled properly, it can be used to make delicious food.

customize.name: Bacon
customize.desc: Smoked strips of pork. Crispy with a bit of fat, but not too greasy. Mmmmm... bacon.

customize.name: Tomates Narbonnaises
customize.desc: A dish with a well-balanced proportion of meat and vegetables. Hollow out a round tomato, fill the hollowed tomato with ground meat, then bake this combination. This dish has a sour flavor and a tender texture. It is a very popular choice on Fontainian tables.

customize.name: Delicious Tomates Narbonnaises
customize.desc: A dish of meat and vegetables. Juicy mouthwatering tomatoes filled with hearty meat, each one has an agile, charming aroma, which explodes into a splendid savor after biting into it. After eating a single one, all the dark clouds in your heart will have been banished by the rich deliciousness emanating from your tongue.

value.text: Increases all party members' ATK by 160 for 300s. In Co-Op Mode, this effect only applies to your own character(s).
